Annotation.note:
If $O$ is the circumcenter and $H$ the orthocenter of a triangle $ABC$, and $AH$, $BH$, $CH$ meet the circumcircle in $D$, $E$, $F$, prove that parallels through $D$, $E$, $F$ to $OA$, $OB$, $OC$, respectively, meet in a point.
\begin{keywords} geometry theorem proving \end{keywords}
